P\lor (P \land Q) \equiv (P\lor P) \land (P \lor Q) \equiv P \land (P \lor Q) \implies P\tag{$\Leftarrow$}
P \iff (P \lor (P \land Q))
\;p \lor q \Leftrightarrow q\;
\;p \Rightarrow q\;
